The paper deals with graph drawing algorithms, specifically for planar graphs with collinear vertices. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses treewidth and cubic planar graphs, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions universal point subsets and column planarity, which are related to information visualization and graph drawing (cs.SI).
